main event: A sighting of an object consistent with the Satellite ECHO II over Sparta, Tennessee on September 3, 1964.
interesting points: The object was observed for 13 minutes, moving from northwest to southeast.
The object was described as looking like a star moving across the sky.
The sighting was made by a civilian witness.
The conclusion of the report was that the sighting was consistent with the Satellite ECHO II, which was the probable cause.
The report includes detailed information about the object's location, altitude, and movement over time.
